  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-leek-and-pea-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s] </strong>in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>soft cheese</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>creamy chicken stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-leek-and-pea-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil a full kettle</p><p>Once the bacon is golden, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-leek-and-pea-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>wholewheat tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>wholewheat tortiglioni</strong> for 10-12 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>wholewheat tortiglioni</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-leek-and-pea-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>creamy chicken stock</strong> to the pan with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until the sauce has thickened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-leek-and-pea-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sauce thickens, grate your <strong>lighter cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-leek-and-pea-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the <strong>cooked wholewheat tortiglioni </strong>and your <strong>blanched peas </strong>to the pan and stir it all together until everything is coated in the sauce – this is your <strong>creamy bacon, leek and pea wholewheat tortiglioni</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-leek-and-pea-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy bacon, leek and pea wholewheat tortiglioni </strong>and top with the <strong>grated lighter cheese</strong> and a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
